{
  "stem": "7358.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The-- the Ukrainian police used to come and start knocking on the doors and-- and wake up all the people in the middle of the night and run and chase them all into the square and line them up in rows.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And people used to come out with their nightclothes, and-- and-- no matter what condition you are at the time of the knock on the window, that's how you had to come out in the street.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And sometimes the people would stay there for hours and wait and didn't know what's-- what's going to happen to them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And-- and-- and suddenly, the commissar arrived on his horse, and he delivered a speech, mostly about cleanliness, about he heard that the ghetto is dirty, and he's going to have inspections-- all kind of nonsense of that kind.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it turned out later on that this was a calculated arrangement.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were always afraid perhaps the Jews would rebel when the final solution would come.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Once they realize they were being taken to die, they thought there would be perhaps some-- some-- the Jews would cause some trouble.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in order to get people used to-- to those meetings-- so every-- every couple of weeks, they would-- they would pull the people out in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And everybody got used to that this is one of the sufferings that we-- we have to-- we have to endure.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and-- but they knew that one of these days when they'll make a decision for the final liquidation of the ghetto that the Jews would already be-- be accustomed to come out to the square.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that's exactly what happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
